Remove unused method in StageTaskSourceFactory
Support coordinator task scheduling in fault tolerant scheduler

Fix FaultTolerantStageScheduler#isFinished

Wait for split enumeration feature to finish before returning true from isFinished

Transition stage to FINISHED state early

In FTE a stage is transtitioned to FINISHED only after query completion.
This was needed to allow certain tasks to be rescheduled to reconstruct
lost data (due to unreliable exchange). This mechanism has never been
utilized and likely will never be as currently the solution is built
under assumption that exchange is reliable.
Abort / cancel tasks only once

Remove FaultTolerantStageSchedule#reportTaskFailure

With only spooling exchange being used in fault tolerant execution
there's no need to report task failures from coordinator what was only
needed with direct exchange

Fail tasks directly through SqlStage

To avoid unnecessary indirections
Extract StageManager into a standalone class

Refactor StageManager

Do not pass session separately as it can be obtained through
QueryStateMachine
Separate fault tolerant and pipelined scheduler implementations

Change data ownership contract in call of ExchangeSink.add

After the change the contract changes in a way that ownership of data
passed as an argument is passed from caller to callee.
Apart from usage in DeduplicatingDirectExchangeBuffer the Slices passed
as to ExchangeSink.add were single-use and not mutataded/reclaimed
afterwards.

The semantics change allows for simplere and more effective
implementations of ExchangeSinks as no extra data copying is enforced.

issue.title: fastly.allowDynamicBackends in version 0.5.4
issue.body:
The current version of `@fastly/js-compute-runtime` at npm is 0.5.4, published 9/28/22. The [changelog](https://unpkg.com/@fastly/js-compute@0.5.4/CHANGELOG.md) mentions that it's now possible to enable dynamic backends with

```javascript
fastly.allowDynamicBackends = true;
```

Running my app with `fastly compute serve` results in an error:

```text
% fastly compute serve
✓ Initializing...
✓ Verifying package manifest...
✓ Verifying local javascript toolchain...
✓ Running [scripts.build]...
✓ Creating package archive...

SUCCESS: Built package (pkg/package.tar.gz)

✓ Running local server...

Oct 14 13:51:46.726 ERROR unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined
Error: Other(unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined)

ERROR: error during execution process:

Oct 14 13:51:46.726 ERROR unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined
Error: Other(unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined).

If you believe this error is the result of a bug, please file an issue: https://github.com/fastly/cli/issues/new?labels=bug&template=bug_report.md
```

I can publish my app to Compute@Edge ok, but at runtime, when I make a request, it fails with

```text
stderr | d177a668 | Error while running request handler: register_dynamic_backend: Unsupported operation error. This error is thrown when some operation cannot be performed, because it is not supported. - Fastly error code 5
stderr | d177a668 | 
stderr | d177a668 | Stack:
stderr | d177a668 |   o@<stdin>:2:219
stderr | d177a668 |   @<stdin>:2:866
stderr | d177a668 |   @<stdin>:2:1381
stderr | d177a668 | 
```

Coming here, I don't see 0.5.4 in the tags, so I'm confused. Did 0.5.4 get released? Was it released, then unreleased? If so, then it needs to be deleted from npm.

Change randomized prefix to contain only hex characters

Some storage systems prefer the prefix to be hexadecimal characters

Disallow table creation in BigQuery with query retries enabled

BigQuery connector doesn't support fault tolerant execution yet.

Now this variable only holds the result of the low bound comparison, so
it could be renamed.

Add main method to S3HiveQueryRunner
Remove unused method in StageTaskSourceFactory
Support coordinator task scheduling in fault tolerant scheduler

Fix FaultTolerantStageScheduler#isFinished

Wait for split enumeration feature to finish before returning true from isFinished

Transition stage to FINISHED state early

In FTE a stage is transtitioned to FINISHED only after query completion.
This was needed to allow certain tasks to be rescheduled to reconstruct
lost data (due to unreliable exchange). This mechanism has never been
utilized and likely will never be as currently the solution is built
under assumption that exchange is reliable.
Abort / cancel tasks only once

Remove FaultTolerantStageSchedule#reportTaskFailure

With only spooling exchange being used in fault tolerant execution
there's no need to report task failures from coordinator what was only
needed with direct exchange

Fail tasks directly through SqlStage

To avoid unnecessary indirections
Extract StageManager into a standalone class

Refactor StageManager

Do not pass session separately as it can be obtained through
QueryStateMachine
Separate fault tolerant and pipelined scheduler implementations

Change data ownership contract in call of ExchangeSink.add

After the change the contract changes in a way that ownership of data
passed as an argument is passed from caller to callee.
Apart from usage in DeduplicatingDirectExchangeBuffer the Slices passed
as to ExchangeSink.add were single-use and not mutataded/reclaimed
afterwards.

The semantics change allows for simplere and more effective
implementations of ExchangeSinks as no extra data copying is enforced.

Check error code for RENAME COLUMN failure in MariaDB

SQLSyntaxErrorException contains invalid column name.

Set SUPPORTS_RENAME_COLUMN as false in unsupported connectors

testRenameColumn was skipped by SUPPORTS_CREATE_TABLE
condition.

issue.body:
The current version of `@fastly/js-compute-runtime` at npm is 0.5.4, published 9/28/22. The [changelog](https://unpkg.com/@fastly/js-compute@0.5.4/CHANGELOG.md) mentions that it's now possible to enable dynamic backends with

```javascript
fastly.allowDynamicBackends = true;
```

Running my app with `fastly compute serve` results in an error:

```text
% fastly compute serve
✓ Initializing...
✓ Verifying package manifest...
✓ Verifying local javascript toolchain...
✓ Running [scripts.build]...
✓ Creating package archive...

SUCCESS: Built package (pkg/package.tar.gz)

✓ Running local server...

Oct 14 13:51:46.726 ERROR unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined
Error: Other(unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined)

ERROR: error during execution process:

Oct 14 13:51:46.726 ERROR unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined
Error: Other(unknown import: `fastly_http_req::register_dynamic_backend` has not been defined).

If you believe this error is the result of a bug, please file an issue: https://github.com/fastly/cli/issues/new?labels=bug&template=bug_report.md
```

I can publish my app to Compute@Edge ok, but at runtime, when I make a request, it fails with

```text
stderr | d177a668 | Error while running request handler: register_dynamic_backend: Unsupported operation error. This error is thrown when some operation cannot be performed, because it is not supported. - Fastly error code 5
stderr | d177a668 | 
stderr | d177a668 | Stack:
stderr | d177a668 |   o@<stdin>:2:219
stderr | d177a668 |   @<stdin>:2:866
stderr | d177a668 |   @<stdin>:2:1381
stderr | d177a668 | 
```

Coming here, I don't see 0.5.4 in the tags, so I'm confused. Did 0.5.4 get released? Was it released, then unreleased? If so, then it needs to be deleted from npm.
